Hey, I’m Drew Slater, the drone pilot, cinematographer, photographer and editor behind AZ Drone Guy LLC. I’ve called Arizona home since 1998 and have always been drawn to hobbies that blend creativity with tech. My love for building and racing RC cars led me to camera drones, and the first live feed I saw while off-roading hooked me instantly.

I trained for hours on simulators and built most of my FPV drones from scratch (the Chimera 7 Pro is the only one I didn’t build). It’s the hardest hobby I’ve tackled, but seeing my home-built drones lift off made every hour worth it.

Now, as an FAA Part 107 certified pilot, I pair cinematic aerial shots with ground footage from my full frame mirrorless and 360 cameras to create clean, engaging videos for local businesses and organizations. Whether it’s showcasing real estate, events or local brands, I help others share their passion with the world through visuals you can’t get any other way.

Let’s create something worth watching. DM me or reach out at arizonadroneguy@gmail.com to get started.
